    <h4 class="h3">I will increase the amount of low-salt alternatives for cooking and food preparation</h4>

    <h5>Common foods that are high in salt are:</h5>

    <ul>
        <li>Soy and Worcestershire sauces, tomato and other vegetable juices, and most cheeses</li>
        <li>Many bottled salad dressings and salad dressing mixes</li>
        <li>Most snack foods, such as chips, crackers, and others</li>
        <li>Processed foods, such as cured or smoked meats, bacon, hot dogs, sausage, bologna, ham, and salami</li>
        <li>Anchovies, olives, pickles, and sauerkraut</li>
    </ul>

